## What I found in the codebase

The chat template system lives in two files:
- **`src/llama-chat.h`** — the internal `llm_chat_template` enum (54 values + `UNKNOWN`)
- **`src/llama-chat.cpp`** — a string→enum registry map, a heuristic `llm_chat_detect_template()` function, and the big `llm_chat_apply_template()` if/else chain

The public header (`include/llama.h`) is untouched. The Ministral 3 specialized handler in `common/chat.cpp` is also untouched.

---

## The 4 changes

### 1. New enum value — `src/llama-chat.h` (line 60, before `UNKNOWN`)
```cpp
LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_MISTRAL_INSTRUCT_V3,
```

### 2. Registry entry — `src/llama-chat.cpp` (inside `LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATES` map, near line 38)
```cpp
{ "mistral-instruct-v3", LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_MISTRAL_INSTRUCT_V3 },
```

### 3. Detection heuristic — `src/llama-chat.cpp` (top of the inner `else` block at ~line 122)

This block is only reached when `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` is **absent** (the outer `if` already ruled it out), making Ministral 3 naturally excluded. The positive fingerprint for Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3's Jinja is the single-quoted `'[INST] '` literal:
```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v0.3: [INST]/[/INST] without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
// (absence of [SYSTEM_PROMPT] is implicit — guaranteed by this else branch)
if (tmpl_contains("'[INST] '")) {
    return LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_MISTRAL_INSTRUCT_V3;
}
```

### 4. Handler — `src/llama-chat.cpp` (new `else if` before the final `else { return -1; }`)
```cpp
} else if (tmpl == LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_MISTRAL_INSTRUCT_V3) {
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3: system prepended to first user turn, [INST]/[/INST], </s> after assistant
    std::string system_message;
    bool is_first_user = true;
    for (auto message : chat) {
        std::string role(message->role);
        std::string content(message->content);
        if (role == "system") {
            system_message = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            ss << "[INST] ";
            if (is_first_user && !system_message.empty()) {
                ss << system_message << "\n\n";
            }
            is_first_user = false;
            ss << content << " [/INST]";
        } else {
            ss << content << "</s>";
        }
    }
    if (add_ass) {
        ss << "[INST] ";
    }
```

**Example:** `system:"Be helpful"` + `user:"Hi"` + `assistant:"Hey"` + `user:"More"` →  
`[INST] Be helpful\n\nHi [/INST]Hey</s>[INST] More [/INST]`
